{
  "video_id": "0JGarsZE1rk",
  "title": "The human stories behind mass incarceration | Eve Abrams",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12869.0,
      "end_time": 14954.0,
      "text": "I have never been arrested,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14978.0,
      "end_time": 16841.0,
      "text": "never spent a night in jail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16865.0,
      "end_time": 20686.0,
      "text": "never had a loved one thrown into the back of a squad car"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20710.0,
      "end_time": 22366.0,
      "text": "or behind bars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22390.0,
      "end_time": 26827.0,
      "text": "or be at the mercy of a scary, confusing system"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26851.0,
      "end_time": 29901.0,
      "text": "that at best sees them with indifference,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29925.0,
      "end_time": 31758.0,
      "text": "and at worst as monstrous."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32459.000000000004,
      "end_time": 36229.0,
      "text": "The United States of America locks up more people than any other nation"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36253.0,
      "end_time": 37660.0,
      "text": "on the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37684.0,
      "end_time": 40590.0,
      "text": "and Louisiana is our biggest incarcerator."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 41295.0,
      "end_time": 44177.0,
      "text": "Most of you are probably like me --"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44201.0,
      "end_time": 45352.0,
      "text": "lucky."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 45376.0,
      "end_time": 49537.0,
      "text": "The closest we get to crime and punishment is likely what we see on TV."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50102.0,
      "end_time": 51433.0,
      "text": "While making \"Unprisoned,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51457.0,
      "end_time": 53759.0,
      "text": "I met a woman who used to be like us --"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53783.0,
      "end_time": 54933.0,
      "text": "Sheila Phipps."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 55572.0,
      "end_time": 58104.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Sheila Phipps: Before my son went to jail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58128.0,
      "end_time": 60108.0,
      "text": "I used to see people be on television,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 60132.0,
      "end_time": 63921.0,
      "text": "fighting, saying, \"Oh, this person didn't do it and this person is innocent.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 63945.0,
      "end_time": 66659.0,
      "text": "And you know, you snub them or you dismiss them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 66683.0,
      "end_time": 68703.0,
      "text": "and like, \"Yeah, whatever.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 68727.0,
      "end_time": 69878.0,
      "text": "Don't get me wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69902.0,
      "end_time": 72406.0,
      "text": "there's a lot of people who deserve to be in prison."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 72430.0,
      "end_time": 74250.0,
      "text": "There's a lot of criminals out here."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 74274.0,
      "end_time": 77473.0,
      "text": "But there are a lot of innocent people that's in jail."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 78436.0,
      "end_time": 81703.0,
      "text": "EA: Sheila's son, McKinley, is one of those innocent people."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 81727.0,
      "end_time": 86587.0,
      "text": "He served 17 years of a 30-year sentence on a manslaughter charge."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 86611.0,
      "end_time": 88410.0,
      "text": "He had no previous convictions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 88434.0,
      "end_time": 91120.0,
      "text": "there was no forensic evidence in the case."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 91360.0,
      "end_time": 95147.0,
      "text": "He was convicted solely on the basis of eyewitness testimony,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 95171.0,
      "end_time": 97330.0,
      "text": "and decades of research have shown"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 97354.0,
      "end_time": 100226.0,
      "text": "that eyewitness testimony isn't as reliable"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 100250.0,
      "end_time": 102150.0,
      "text": "as we once believed it to be."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 102750.0,
      "end_time": 105694.0,
      "text": "Scientists say that memory isn't precise."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 106120.0,
      "end_time": 108551.0,
      "text": "It's less like playing back a video,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 108575.0,
      "end_time": 111260.0,
      "text": "and more like putting together a puzzle."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 111997.0,
      "end_time": 117489.0,
      "text": "Since 1989, when DNA testing was first used to free innocent people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117513.0,
      "end_time": 122962.0,
      "text": "over 70 percent of overturned convictions were based on eyewitness testimony."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 123784.0,
      "end_time": 125900.0,
      "text": "Last year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125114.0,
      "end_time": 128993.0,
      "text": "the district attorney whose office prosecuted McKinley's case"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129169.99999999999,
      "end_time": 132503.0,
      "text": "was convicted of unrelated corruption charges."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132930.0,
      "end_time": 136765.0,
      "text": "When this district attorney of 30 years stepped down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 136789.0,
      "end_time": 139716.0,
      "text": "the eyewitnesses from McKinley's case came forward"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 139741.0,
      "end_time": 144200.0,
      "text": "and said that they had been pressured into testifying by the district attorneys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 144224.0,
      "end_time": 147105.0,
      "text": "pressure which included the threat of jail time."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 147465.0,
      "end_time": 150392.0,
      "text": "Despite this, McKinley is still in prison."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 151990.0,
      "end_time": 152981.0,
      "text": "(Recording) SP: Before this happened,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153500.0,
      "end_time": 154460.0,
      "text": "I never would've thought it."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 154485.0,
      "end_time": 158115.0,
      "text": "And well, I guess it's hard for me to imagine"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 158139.0,
      "end_time": 160695.0,
      "text": "that these things is going on, you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 160719.0,
      "end_time": 162971.0,
      "text": "until this happened to my son."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 163504.0,
      "end_time": 165143.0,
      "text": "It really opened my eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 165618.0,
      "end_time": 168670.0,
      "text": "It really, really opened my eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168920.0,
      "end_time": 169546.0,
      "text": "I ain't gonna lie to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 170850.0,
      "end_time": 173963.0,
      "text": "EA: Estimates of how many innocent people are locked up"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 173987.0,
      "end_time": 176677.0,
      "text": "range between one and four percent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 176701.0,
      "end_time": 178707.0,
      "text": "which maybe doesn't sound like a lot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 178731.0,
      "end_time": 182916.0,
      "text": "except that it amounts to around 87,000 people:"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 182940.0,
      "end_time": 186314.0,
      "text": "mothers, fathers, sons locked up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 186338.0,
      "end_time": 187686.0,
      "text": "often for decades,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 187711.0,
      "end_time": 189917.0,
      "text": "for crimes they did not commit."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 189941.0,
      "end_time": 193130.0,
      "text": "And that's not even counting the roughly half a million people"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 193370.0,
      "end_time": 195269.0,
      "text": "who have been convicted of nothing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 195293.0,
      "end_time": 197166.0,
      "text": "those presumed innocent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 197190.0,
      "end_time": 200230.0,
      "text": "but who are too poor to bail out of jail"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 200470.0,
      "end_time": 203906.0,
      "text": "and therefore sit behind bars for weeks upon months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 203930.0,
      "end_time": 206990.0,
      "text": "waiting for their case to come to trial --"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 206123.0,
      "end_time": 207804.0,
      "text": "or much more likely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 207828.0,
      "end_time": 210184.0,
      "text": "waiting to take a plea just to get out."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 210736.0,
      "end_time": 213858.0,
      "text": "All of those people have family on the outside."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 215890.0,
      "end_time": 218518.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Kortney Williams: My brother missed my high school graduation"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 218542.0,
      "end_time": 219793.0,
      "text": "because the night before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 219817.0,
      "end_time": 221318.0,
      "text": "he went to jail."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 221342.0,
      "end_time": 223587.0,
      "text": "My brother missed my birthday dinner"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 223611.0,
      "end_time": 226588.0,
      "text": "because that day, actually, he went to jail."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 227306.0,
      "end_time": 230146.0,
      "text": "My brother missed his own birthday dinner"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 230170.0,
      "end_time": 232629.0,
      "text": "because he was in the wrong place at the wrong time."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 232653.0,
      "end_time": 235749.0,
      "text": "(Recording) EA: So all these times when he ended up going to jail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 235773.0,
      "end_time": 238297.0,
      "text": "were charges pressed or did he just get taken to jail?"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 238321.0,
      "end_time": 239872.0,
      "text": "KW: The charges would be pressed"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 239896.0,
      "end_time": 242922.0,
      "text": "and it would have a bond posted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 242946.0,
      "end_time": 244913.0,
      "text": "then the charges will get dropped ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 244937.0,
      "end_time": 246391.0,
      "text": "because there was no evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 247248.0,
      "end_time": 250202.0,
      "text": "EA: I met Kortney Williams when I went to her college classroom"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 250226.0,
      "end_time": 251717.0,
      "text": "to talk about \"Unprisoned.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 251741.0,
      "end_time": 255136.0,
      "text": "She ended up interviewing her aunt, Troylynn Robertson,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 255160.0,
      "end_time": 256310.0,
      "text": "for an episode."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 257231.0,
      "end_time": 259709.0,
      "text": "(Recording) KW: With everything that you went through"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 259733.0,
      "end_time": 260884.0,
      "text": "with your children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 260908.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262890.0,
      "text": "what is any advice that you would give me"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 262914.0,
      "end_time": 264823.0,
      "text": "if I had any kids?"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 265827.0,
      "end_time": 269580.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Troylynn Roberston: I would tell you when you have them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 269820.0,
      "end_time": 272138.0,
      "text": "you know the first thing that will initially come to mind is love"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 272162.0,
      "end_time": 274133.0,
      "text": "and protection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 274158.0,
      "end_time": 275654.0,
      "text": "but I would tell you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 275678.0,
      "end_time": 278766.0,
      "text": "even much with the protection to raise them"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 278790.0,
      "end_time": 282496.0,
      "text": "with knowledge of the judicial system --"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 282520.0,
      "end_time": 286990.0,
      "text": "you know, we always tell our kids about the boogeyman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 286124.0,
      "end_time": 289117.0,
      "text": "the bad people, who to watch out for,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 289141.0,
      "end_time": 293690.0,
      "text": "but we don't teach them how to watch out for the judicial system."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 294364.0,
      "end_time": 297300.0,
      "text": "EA: Because of the way our criminal legal system"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 297550.0,
      "end_time": 299691.0,
      "text": "disproportionately targets people of color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 299715.0,
      "end_time": 303800.0,
      "text": "it's not uncommon for young people like Kortney to know about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 303494.0,
      "end_time": 307336.0,
      "text": "When I started going into high schools to talk to students about \"Unprisoned,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 307360.0,
      "end_time": 310853.0,
      "text": "I found that roughly one-third of the young people I spoke with"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 310877.0,
      "end_time": 312763.0,
      "text": "had a loved one behind bars."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 313504.0,
      "end_time": 316743.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Girl: The hardest part is like finding out where he's at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 316767.0,
      "end_time": 318368.0,
      "text": "or like, when his court date is."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 318759.0,
      "end_time": 321477.0,
      "text": "Girl: Yeah, he went to jail on my first birthday."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 322415.0,
      "end_time": 324418.0,
      "text": "Girl: My dad works as a guard."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 324442.0,
      "end_time": 325970.0,
      "text": "He saw my uncle in jail."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 326527.0,
      "end_time": 327743.0,
      "text": "He's in there for life."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 328434.0,
      "end_time": 331103.0,
      "text": "EA: According to the Annie E. Casey Foundation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 331127.0,
      "end_time": 336980.0,
      "text": "the number of young people with a father incarcerated rose 500 percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 337400.0,
      "end_time": 339818.0,
      "text": "between 1980 and 2000."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 340449.0,
      "end_time": 344356.0,
      "text": "Over five million of today's children will see a parent incarcerated"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 344380.0,
      "end_time": 346322.0,
      "text": "at some point in their childhoods."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 346798.0,
      "end_time": 351321.0,
      "text": "But this number disproportionately affects African American children."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 352252.0,
      "end_time": 354943.0,
      "text": "By the time they reach the age of 14,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 354967.0,
      "end_time": 358740.0,
      "text": "one in four black children will see their dad go off to prison."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 359198.0,
      "end_time": 362592.0,
      "text": "That's compared to a rate of one in 30 for white children."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 363191.0,
      "end_time": 368268.0,
      "text": "One key factor determining the future success of both inmates and their children"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 368293.0,
      "end_time": 372642.0,
      "text": "is whether they can maintain ties during the parent's incarceration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 372666.0,
      "end_time": 377900.0,
      "text": "but prisoners' phone calls home can cost 20 to 30 times more"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 377330.0,
      "end_time": 378886.0,
      "text": "than regular phone calls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 378910.0,
      "end_time": 382117.0,
      "text": "so many families keep in touch through letters."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 383172.0,
      "end_time": 385357.0,
      "text": "(Recording: Letter being unfolded)"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 385381.0,
      "end_time": 387587.0,
      "text": "Anissa Christmas: Dear big brother,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 387612.0,
      "end_time": 389443.0,
      "text": "I'm making that big 16 this year, LOL."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 389934.0,
      "end_time": 391593.0,
      "text": "Guess I'm not a baby anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 391617.0,
      "end_time": 393226.0,
      "text": "You still taking me to prom?"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 393250.0,
      "end_time": 394499.0,
      "text": "I really miss you."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 394523.0,
      "end_time": 396735.0,
      "text": "You're the only guy that kept it real with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 397485.0,
      "end_time": 400102.0,
      "text": "I wish you were here so I can vent to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 400695.0,
      "end_time": 403286.0,
      "text": "So much has happened since the last time I seen you."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 404847.0,
      "end_time": 406909.0,
      "text": "(Voice breaking up) I have some good news."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 406933.0,
      "end_time": 408766.0,
      "text": "I won first place in the science fair."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 408790.0,
      "end_time": 409981.0,
      "text": "I'm a geek."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 410500.0,
      "end_time": 412271.0,
      "text": "We're going to regionals, can't you believe it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 412295.0,
      "end_time": 414470.0,
      "text": "High school is going by super fast."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 414893.0,
      "end_time": 416700.0,
      "text": "In less than two years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 416950.0,
      "end_time": 418709.0,
      "text": "I hope you'll be able to see me walk across the stage."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 419413.0,
      "end_time": 422318.0,
      "text": "I thought to write to you because I know it's boring in there."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 422342.0,
      "end_time": 424540.0,
      "text": "I want to put a smile on your face."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 425799.0,
      "end_time": 428770.0,
      "text": "Anissa wrote these letters to her brother"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 428101.0,
      "end_time": 430323.0,
      "text": "when she was a sophomore in high school."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 430347.0,
      "end_time": 433277.0,
      "text": "She keeps the letters he writes to her tucked into the frame"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 433302.0,
      "end_time": 434480.0,
      "text": "of her bedroom mirror,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 434504.0,
      "end_time": 436543.0,
      "text": "and reads them over and over again."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 437400.0,
      "end_time": 439117.0,
      "text": "I'd like to think that there's a good reason"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 439141.0,
      "end_time": 441519.0,
      "text": "why Anissa's brother is locked up."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 441543.0,
      "end_time": 445600.0,
      "text": "We all want the wheels of justice to properly turn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 445624.0,
      "end_time": 447432.0,
      "text": "but we're coming to understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 447456.0,
      "end_time": 450980.0,
      "text": "that the lofty ideals we learned in school look really different"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 451400.0,
      "end_time": 454337.0,
      "text": "in our nation's prisons and jails and courtrooms."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 454943.0,
      "end_time": 458515.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Danny Engelberg: You walk into that courtroom and you're just --"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 458540.0,
      "end_time": 462730.0,
      "text": "I've been doing this for a quite a while, and it still catches your breath."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 462970.0,
      "end_time": 464635.0,
      "text": "You're like, \"There are so many people of color here,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 464659.0,
      "end_time": 469629.0,
      "text": "and yet I know that the city is not made up of 90 percent African Americans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 469653.0,
      "end_time": 473149.0,
      "text": "so why is it that 90 percent of the people who are in orange"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 473173.0,
      "end_time": 474324.0,
      "text": "are African American?"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 474348.0,
      "end_time": 477907.0,
      "text": "(Recording) EA: Public defender Danny Engelberg isn't the only one noticing"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 477931.0,
      "end_time": 480121.0,
      "text": "how many black people are in municipal court --"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 480146.0,
      "end_time": 481298.0,
      "text": "or in any court."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 481322.0,
      "end_time": 482500.0,
      "text": "It's hard to miss."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 482524.0,
      "end_time": 484795.0,
      "text": "Who's sitting in court waiting to see the judge?"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 484819.0,
      "end_time": 486200.0,
      "text": "What do they look like?"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 486440.0,
      "end_time": 488513.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Man: Mostly African-Americans, like me."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 488537.0,
      "end_time": 490792.0,
      "text": "Man: It's mostly, I could say, 85 percent black."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 490816.0,
      "end_time": 494215.0,
      "text": "That's all you see in the orange, in the box back there, who locked up."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 494239.0,
      "end_time": 496633.0,
      "text": "Man: Who's waiting? Mostly black."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 496657.0,
      "end_time": 499135.0,
      "text": "I mean, there was a couple of white people in there."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 499160.0,
      "end_time": 501733.0,
      "text": "Woman: I think it was about 85 percent African-American"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 501757.0,
      "end_time": 502954.0,
      "text": "that was sitting there."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 503923.0,
      "end_time": 507731.0,
      "text": "EA: How does a young black person growing up in America today"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 507755.0,
      "end_time": 510147.0,
      "text": "come to understand justice?"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 510696.0,
      "end_time": 513839.0,
      "text": "Another \"Unprisoned\" story was about a troupe of dancers"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 513863.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516173.00000000006,
      "text": "who choreographed a piece called \"Hoods Up,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 516197.0,
      "end_time": 518347.0,
      "text": "which they performed in front of city council."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 518832.99999999994,
      "end_time": 522408.99999999994,
      "text": "Dawonta White was in the seventh grade for that performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 522986.0,
      "end_time": 527177.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Dawonta White: We was wearing black with hoodies because Trayvon Martin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 527201.0,
      "end_time": 529488.0,
      "text": "when he was wearing his hoodie, he was killed."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 529512.0,
      "end_time": 530867.0,
      "text": "So we looked upon that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 530892.0,
      "end_time": 533704.0,
      "text": "and we said we're going to wear hoodies like Trayvon Martin."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 533728.0,
      "end_time": 535846.0,
      "text": "(Recording) EA: Who came up with that idea?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 535870.0,
      "end_time": 537537.0,
      "text": "DW: The group. We all agreed on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 537561.0,
      "end_time": 540305.0,
      "text": "I was a little nervous, but I had stick through it though,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 540329.0,
      "end_time": 544577.0,
      "text": "but I felt like it was a good thing so they could notice what we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 544601.0,
      "end_time": 547793.0,
      "text": "(Recording) EA: Shraivell Brown was another choreographer and dancer"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 547817.0,
      "end_time": 549590.0,
      "text": "in \"Hoods Up.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 549830.0,
      "end_time": 551644.0,
      "text": "He says the police criticize people who look like him."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 551668.0,
      "end_time": 555320.0,
      "text": "He feels judged based on things other black people may have done."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 555560.0,
      "end_time": 557192.0,
      "text": "How would you want the police to look at you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 557206.0,
      "end_time": 559250.0,
      "text": "and what would you want them to think?"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 559490.0,
      "end_time": 560348.0,
      "text": "SB: That I'm not no threat."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 560372.0,
      "end_time": 562420.0,
      "text": "EA: Why would they think you're threatening?"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 562445.0,
      "end_time": 563843.0,
      "text": "What did you say, you're 14?"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 563867.0,
      "end_time": 569430.0,
      "text": "SB: Yes, I'm 14, but because he said a lot of black males"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 569670.0,
      "end_time": 572340.0,
      "text": "are thugs or gangsters and all that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 572580.0,
      "end_time": 574588.0,
      "text": "but I don't want them thinking that about me."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 575855.0,
      "end_time": 577598.0,
      "text": "EA: For folks who look like me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 577622.0,
      "end_time": 581925.0,
      "text": "the easiest and most comfortable thing to do is to not pay attention --"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 581949.0,
      "end_time": 585591.0,
      "text": "to assume our criminal legal system is working."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 585615.0,
      "end_time": 590101.0,
      "text": "But if it's not our responsibility to question those assumptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 590125.0,
      "end_time": 592292.0,
      "text": "whose responsibility is it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 593100.0,
      "end_time": 596713.0,
      "text": "There's a synagogue here that's taken on learning about mass incarceration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 596737.0,
      "end_time": 598819.0,
      "text": "and many congregants have concluded"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 598844.0,
      "end_time": 602995.0,
      "text": "that because mass incarceration throws so many lives into chaos,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 603190.0,
      "end_time": 605218.0,
      "text": "it actually creates more crime --"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 605242.0,
      "end_time": 607670.0,
      "text": "makes people less safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 607690.0,
      "end_time": 609639.0,
      "text": "Congregant Teri Hunter says"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 609663.0,
      "end_time": 613131.0,
      "text": "the first step towards action has to be understanding."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 613467.0,
      "end_time": 618996.0,
      "text": "She says it's crucial for all of us to understand our connection to this issue"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 619200.0,
      "end_time": 621788.0,
      "text": "even if it's not immediately obvious."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 623960.0,
      "end_time": 625276.0,
      "text": "(Recording) Teri Hunter: It's on our shoulders"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 625300.0,
      "end_time": 628861.0,
      "text": "to make sure that we're not just closing that door"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 628885.0,
      "end_time": 630470.0,
      "text": "and saying, \"Well, it's not us.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 630842.0,
      "end_time": 635199.0,
      "text": "And I think as Jews, you know, we've lived that history:"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 635224.0,
      "end_time": 636374.0,
      "text": "\"It's not us.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 637420.0,
      "end_time": 641706.0,
      "text": "And so if a society closes their back on one section,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 641730.0,
      "end_time": 643412.0,
      "text": "we've seen what happens."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 643436.0,
      "end_time": 646627.0,
      "text": "And so it is our responsibility as Jews"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 646651.0,
      "end_time": 650214.0,
      "text": "and as members of this community"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 650238.0,
      "end_time": 653429.0,
      "text": "to educate our community --"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 653453.0,
      "end_time": 656358.0,
      "text": "at least our congregation --"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 656382.0,
      "end_time": 658342.0,
      "text": "to the extent that we're able."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 659477.0,
      "end_time": 662738.0,
      "text": "EA: I've been using the pronouns \"us\" and \"we\""
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 662763.0,
      "end_time": 665759.0,
      "text": "because this is our criminal legal system"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 665783.0,
      "end_time": 667132.0,
      "text": "and our children."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 667583.0,
      "end_time": 669752.0,
      "text": "We elect the district attorneys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 669776.0,
      "end_time": 673819.0,
      "text": "the judges and the legislators who operate these systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 673844.0,
      "end_time": 674994.0,
      "text": "for we the people."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 675677.0,
      "end_time": 676964.0,
      "text": "As a society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 676988.0,
      "end_time": 680589.0,
      "text": "we are more willing to risk locking up innocent people"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 680613.0,
      "end_time": 683503.0,
      "text": "than we are to let guilty people go free."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 684187.0,
      "end_time": 687696.0,
      "text": "We elect politicians who fear being labeled \"soft on crime,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 687720.0,
      "end_time": 690712.0,
      "text": "encouraging them to pass harsh legislation"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 690736.0,
      "end_time": 694980.0,
      "text": "and allocate enormous resources toward locking people up."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 695452.0,
      "end_time": 697116.0,
      "text": "When a crime is committed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 697140.0,
      "end_time": 701894.0,
      "text": "our hunger for swift retribution has fed a police culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 701918.0,
      "end_time": 704758.0,
      "text": "bent on finding culprits fast,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 704782.0,
      "end_time": 709295.0,
      "text": "often without adequate resources to conduct thorough investigations"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 709319.0,
      "end_time": 712410.0,
      "text": "or strict scrutiny of those investigations."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 712926.0,
      "end_time": 716250.0,
      "text": "We don't put checks on prosecutors."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 716514.0,
      "end_time": 719650.0,
      "text": "Across the country, over the last couple of decades,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 719674.0,
      "end_time": 723769.0,
      "text": "as property and violent crimes have both fell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 723793.0,
      "end_time": 728661.0,
      "text": "the number of prosecutors employed and cases they have filed has risen."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 729341.0,
      "end_time": 732480.0,
      "text": "Prosecutors decide whether or not to take legal action"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 732720.0,
      "end_time": 734101.0,
      "text": "against the people police arrest"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 734125.0,
      "end_time": 737122.0,
      "text": "and they decide what charges to file,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 737146.0,
      "end_time": 742899.0,
      "text": "directly impacting how much time a defendant potentially faces behind bars."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 743706.0,
      "end_time": 747593.0,
      "text": "One check we do have on prosecutors is defense."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 747943.0,
      "end_time": 749635.0,
      "text": "Imagine Lady Liberty:"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 749659.0,
      "end_time": 752800.0,
      "text": "the blindfolded woman holding the scale"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 752104.0,
      "end_time": 755284.0,
      "text": "meant to symbolize the balance in our judicial system."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 755854.0,
      "end_time": 759660.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, that scale is tipped."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 759480.0,
      "end_time": 761616.0,
      "text": "The majority of defendants in our country"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 761640.0,
      "end_time": 765210.0,
      "text": "are represented by government-appointed attorneys."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 765460.0,
      "end_time": 769181.0,
      "text": "These public defenders receive around 30 percent less funding"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 769205.0,
      "end_time": 770943.0,
      "text": "than district attorneys do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 770967.0,
      "end_time": 774124.0,
      "text": "and they often have caseloads far outnumbering"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 774148.0,
      "end_time": 776665.0,
      "text": "what the American Bar Association recommends."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 777466.0,
      "end_time": 779332.0,
      "text": "As Sheila Phipps said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 779356.0,
      "end_time": 782289.0,
      "text": "there are people who belong in prison,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 782313.0,
      "end_time": 785813.0,
      "text": "but it's hard to tell the guilty from the innocent"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 785837.0,
      "end_time": 789190.0,
      "text": "when everyone's outcomes are so similar."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 789603.0,
      "end_time": 791117.0,
      "text": "We all want justice."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 791830.0,
      "end_time": 795334.0,
      "text": "But with the process weighed so heavily against defendants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 795358.0,
      "end_time": 797940.0,
      "text": "justice is hard to come by."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 798376.0,
      "end_time": 802790.0,
      "text": "Our criminal legal system operates for we the people."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 802534.0,
